<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-441-710  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 441 710.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 7 1990 n366 p146(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Magneto-optical technology slated to impact mass-storage market innext five years. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gillooly, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Magneto-optical technology combines the reliability and storagecapacity of optical communications with the rewritablefunctionality of conventional magnetic systems.andP;  It is expected toestablish itself as the mass-storage technology of the futurewithin the next five years.andP;  Though currently available,magneto-optical drives now stand at a disadvantage compared toWinchester disks.andP;  They are capable of access times of 70milliseconds for a 300Mbyte disk, compared to Winchester's 20millisecond time for a disk of comparable size.andP;  Magneto-opticaldevices utilize two passes of a laser beam for writing and readingdata onto the disk.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TechnologyOptical CommunicationsMagneto-Optical Disk DrivesInformation Storage and RetrievalLasers.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Tomorrow's technology: magneto-optical rewritable storage. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>